-- Portugal First-Quarter Retail Sales Drop 3.7%, Association Says
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-06-26T15:10:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-26/portugal-first-quarter-retail-sales-drop-3-7-association-says.html
Portuguese retail sales fell 3.7
percent in the first quarter from a year earlier, the Portuguese
Association of Distribution Companies said.  Sales declined to 4.55 billion euros ($5.7 billion) in the
first three months of the year from 4.73 billion euros, APED,
which represents retailers in  Portugal  such as  Jeronimo Martins
SGPS SA (JMT) ’s Pingo Doce unit and  Sonae (SON)  SGPS SA’s Continente
supermarkets, said in an e-mailed statement today.  For Related News and Information:
